<li>I know an apology doesn't undo what I’ve done, but I sincerely regret hurting you.</li>
<li>Please accept my deepest apologies.  I value our family more than words can say.</li>
<li>I'm so sorry for causing you pain. I'll strive to be a better [son/daughter/sibling/parent]</li>
<li>I understand if you need time, but I want you to know how sorry I am.</li>
<li>I feel terrible for the pain I caused.  I’ll work hard to rebuild your trust.</li>
<li>My actions don't reflect how much I cherish our relationship. I sincerely apologize.</li>
<li>I promise to do better. Please believe me when I say I'm truly sorry.</li>
<li>Forgive me, I truly regret my actions and how they impacted you.</li>
<li>I'm sorry for everything. I'll do whatever it takes to repair the damage.</li>
    

